Simple REST / SMTP gate based on Erlang
---------------------------------------

Build:

  $ make

Edit config in "include/restmail.hrl" file.

Local testing.

Start server in foreground:

  $ ./start.sh

Test with Python shell:

  $ python

  >>> import httplib2, json
  >>> h = httplib2.Http()

  >>> msg = json.dumps({"recipients": ["test1@example.com", "test2@example.com"],
                        "subject": "Welcome",
			"body": "<h1>The body of this message</h2>"})

  >>> r,c = h.request("http://localhost:9004/mail",
                       method="POST",
		       body=msg,
		       headers={"Content-Type":"application/json"})
